{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RWqJivRp1gLjMUjEgJ6AHx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 12-3: Move Business Logic from status.ts Command to Status Module\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want `src/commands/status.ts` under 100 lines with logic in `src/modules/status/`,\n     9→So that status logic is testable without command wiring.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given `src/modules/status/` with `index.ts`, `formatters.ts`, `endpoints.ts`, `drill-down.ts`, when `src/commands/status.ts` is inspected, then it's under 100 lines -- just arg parsing, module call, output formatting <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given `src/modules/status/endpoints.ts`, when `buildScopedEndpoints()` is called, then it produces the same URLs as the current `status.ts` implementation <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→\n    16→## Technical Notes\n    17→\n    18→**Decision 8 (Thin Commands, Fat Modules)** and **NFR5** (commands <100 lines). `src/commands/status.ts` is currently 744 lines -- the second worst violator.\n    19→\n    20→Target structure (from architecture-v3.md):\n    21→\n    22→```\n    23→src/modules/status/\n    24→  index.ts        — getStatus(), formatOutput() public API\n    25→  formatters.ts   — Human-readable and JSON formatting for status output\n    26→  endpoints.ts    — URL builders for observability endpoints (Victoria/ELK/remote)\n    27→  drill-down.ts   — Story detail logic (--story <key> deep dive)\n    28→```\n    29→\n    30→The thin command pattern:\n    31→```typescript\n    32→// src/commands/status.ts — target: <100 lines\n    33→export function registerStatusCommand(program: Command): void {\n    34→  program.command('status')\n    35→    .option('--check-docker', '...')\n    36→    .option('--story <key>', '...')\n    37→    .action(async (options) => {\n    38→      const result = await statusModule.getStatus(options);\n    39→      if (isOk(result)) {\n    40→        statusModule.formatOutput(result.data, options);\n    41→      } else {\n    42→        fail(result.error);\n    43→      }\n    44→    });\n    45→}\n    46→```\n    47→\n    48→Current `src/commands/status.ts` contains:\n    49→- CLI arg parsing (keep in command)\n    50→- Sprint state reading and aggregation (move to `index.ts`)\n    51→- URL construction for observability dashboards (move to `endpoints.ts`)\n    52→- Human-readable table/tree formatting (move to `formatters.ts`)\n    53→- Story drill-down with AC status, retry history (move to `drill-down.ts`)\n    54→\n    55→Note: `src/modules/sprint/drill-down.ts` already exists. The new `src/modules/status/drill-down.ts` handles status-command-specific presentation, while `src/modules/sprint/drill-down.ts` handles sprint-level story detail. They may need to be reconciled -- check for overlap.\n    56→\n    57→`buildScopedEndpoints()` must produce identical URLs to the current implementation. Write a comparison test.\n    58→\n    59→## Files to Change\n    60→\n    61→- `src/modules/status/index.ts` — Create. `getStatus()` reads sprint-state.json and aggregates, `formatOutput()` dispatches to formatters\n    62→- `src/modules/status/formatters.ts` — Create. Table and tree formatting for human-readable output, JSON formatting\n    63→- `src/modules/status/endpoints.ts` — Create. `buildScopedEndpoints()` URL builders for Victoria/ELK/remote endpoints\n    64→- `src/modules/status/drill-down.ts` — Create. Story detail view with AC status, retry history, timeline\n    65→- `src/commands/status.ts` — Gut to <100 lines: arg parsing, call status module, format output\n    66→- `src/modules/status/__tests__/endpoints.test.ts` — Create. Verify URL generation matches current implementation\n    67→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01LFLA8oQXWrijK9MtY4zgZk","session_id":"a74f233b-d75f-4731-af98-d5f8de661326","uuid":"a70a5bba-8764-474f-809c-3c8a2c1062e8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:34:43.296Z"}
