{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015wWmxpk4fkdf9HMbiGDjVa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 12-3: Move Business Logic from status.ts Command to Status Module\n     2→\n     3→## Status: review\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want `src/commands/status.ts` under 100 lines with logic in `src/modules/status/`,\n     9→So that status logic is testable without command wiring.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [x] AC1: Given `src/modules/status/` with `index.ts`, `formatters.ts`, `endpoints.ts`, `drill-down.ts`, when `src/commands/status.ts` is inspected, then it's under 100 lines -- just arg parsing, module call, output formatting <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [x] AC2: Given `src/modules/status/endpoints.ts`, when `buildScopedEndpoints()` is called, then it produces the same URLs as the current `status.ts` implementation <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→\n    16→## Technical Notes\n    17→\n    18→**Decision 8 (Thin Commands, Fat Modules)** and **NFR5** (commands <100 lines). `src/commands/status.ts` is currently 744 lines -- the second worst violator.\n    19→\n    20→Target structure (from architecture-v3.md):\n    21→\n    22→```\n    23→src/modules/status/\n    24→  index.ts        — getStatus(), formatOutput() public API\n    25→  formatters.ts   — Human-readable and JSON formatting for status output\n    26→  endpoints.ts    — URL builders for observability endpoints (Victoria/ELK/remote)\n    27→  drill-down.ts   — Story detail logic (--story <key> deep dive)\n    28→```\n    29→\n    30→The thin command pattern:\n    31→```typescript\n    32→// src/commands/status.ts — target: <100 lines\n    33→export function registerStatusCommand(program: Command): void {\n    34→  program.command('status')\n    35→    .option('--check-docker', '...')\n    36→    .option('--story <key>', '...')\n    37→    .action(async (options) => {\n    38→      const result = await statusModule.getStatus(options);\n    39→      if (isOk(result)) {\n    40→        statusModule.formatOutput(result.data, options);\n    41→      } else {\n    42→        fail(result.error);\n    43→      }\n    44→    });\n    45→}\n    46→```\n    47→\n    48→Current `src/commands/status.ts` contains:\n    49→- CLI arg parsing (keep in command)\n    50→- Sprint state reading and aggregation (move to `index.ts`)\n    51→- URL construction for observability dashboards (move to `endpoints.ts`)\n    52→- Human-readable table/tree formatting (move to `formatters.ts`)\n    53→- Story drill-down with AC status, retry history (move to `drill-down.ts`)\n    54→\n    55→Note: `src/modules/sprint/drill-down.ts` already exists. The new `src/modules/status/drill-down.ts` handles status-command-specific presentation, while `src/modules/sprint/drill-down.ts` handles sprint-level story detail. They may need to be reconciled -- check for overlap.\n    56→\n    57→`buildScopedEndpoints()` must produce identical URLs to the current implementation. Write a comparison test.\n    58→\n    59→## Tasks/Subtasks\n    60→\n    61→- [x] Task 1: Create `src/modules/status/endpoints.ts` with `buildScopedEndpoints()`, `resolveEndpoints()`, `DEFAULT_ENDPOINTS`, and types (`EndpointUrls`, `ScopedEndpointUrls`)\n    62→- [x] Task 2: Create `src/modules/status/formatters.ts` with `handleFullStatus()`, `handleDockerCheck()`, `handleHealthCheck()`, and all supporting helpers (sprint state, beads, onboarding, validation)\n    63→- [x] Task 3: Create `src/modules/status/drill-down.ts` with `handleStoryDrillDown()` for story detail presentation (human + JSON)\n    64→- [x] Task 4: Create `src/modules/status/index.ts` as the module public API, re-exporting from endpoints, formatters, and drill-down\n    65→- [x] Task 5: Rewrite `src/commands/status.ts` as thin command (<100 lines) that delegates to the module, with backward-compatible re-exports\n    66→- [x] Task 6: Create `src/modules/status/__tests__/endpoints.test.ts` with comparison tests verifying identical URL generation\n    67→- [x] Task 7: Add `'status'` to `MODULE_NAMES` in `src/modules/__tests__/import-boundaries.test.ts`\n    68→- [x] Task 8: Run full test suite — all 3493 tests pass, zero regressions\n    69→\n    70→## Files to Change\n    71→\n    72→- `src/modules/status/index.ts` — Create. `getStatus()` reads sprint-state.json and aggregates, `formatOutput()` dispatches to formatters\n    73→- `src/modules/status/formatters.ts` — Create. Table and tree formatting for human-readable output, JSON formatting\n    74→- `src/modules/status/endpoints.ts` — Create. `buildScopedEndpoints()` URL builders for Victoria/ELK/remote endpoints\n    75→- `src/modules/status/drill-down.ts` — Create. Story detail view with AC status, retry history, timeline\n    76→- `src/commands/status.ts` — Gut to <100 lines: arg parsing, call status module, format output\n    77→- `src/modules/status/__tests__/endpoints.test.ts` — Create. Verify URL generation matches current implementation\n    78→\n    79→## File List\n    80→\n    81→- `src/modules/status/endpoints.ts` — Created. EndpointUrls, ScopedEndpointUrls types; DEFAULT_ENDPOINTS constant; buildScopedEndpoints() and resolveEndpoints() functions\n    82→- `src/modules/status/formatters.ts` — Created. handleFullStatus(), handleFullStatusJson(), handleHealthCheck(), handleDockerCheck(), and all sprint/beads/onboarding/validation helpers\n    83→- `src/modules/status/drill-down.ts` — Created. handleStoryDrillDown() with human-readable and JSON formatting\n    84→- `src/modules/status/index.ts` — Created. Module public API re-exporting from endpoints, formatters, drill-down\n    85→- `src/commands/status.ts` — Modified. Reduced from 745 lines to 56 lines; delegates to status module; backward-compatible re-exports\n    86→- `src/modules/status/__tests__/endpoints.test.ts` — Created. 15 tests covering buildScopedEndpoints, resolveEndpoints, DEFAULT_ENDPOINTS with comparison test\n    87→- `src/modules/__tests__/import-boundaries.test.ts` — Modified. Added 'status' to MODULE_NAMES\n    88→\n    89→## Change Log\n    90→\n    91→- 2026-03-24: Extracted all business logic from `src/commands/status.ts` (745 lines) into `src/modules/status/` module (4 files). Command reduced to 56 lines. All 80 existing command tests + 15 new endpoint tests pass. Full suite: 3493 tests, 0 regressions.\n    92→\n    93→## Dev Agent Record\n    94→\n    95→### Implementation Plan\n    96→\n    97→Followed the \"Thin Commands, Fat Modules\" pattern (Decision 8, NFR5). Extracted logic into four module files:\n    98→- `endpoints.ts`: Pure functions for URL building and endpoint resolution\n    99→- `formatters.ts`: All status display logic (full status, docker check, health check) with sprint/beads/onboarding/validation helpers\n   100→- `drill-down.ts`: Story drill-down presentation layer (delegates data fetching to sprint module)\n   101→- `index.ts`: Clean public API re-exporting from submodules\n   102→\n   103→The command file retains backward-compatible re-exports (`buildScopedEndpoints`, `DEFAULT_ENDPOINTS`, `EndpointUrls`, `ScopedEndpointUrls`) so existing consumers (including `src/commands/__tests__/status.test.ts`) continue to work without modification.\n   104→\n   105→### Completion Notes\n   106→\n   107→- `src/commands/status.ts` reduced from 745 to 56 lines (92% reduction, well under 100-line target)\n   108→- `src/modules/status/drill-down.ts` handles status-command presentation only; `src/modules/sprint/drill-down.ts` handles sprint data extraction. No overlap — clean separation.\n   109→- The endpoint comparison test explicitly verifies URL generation formula matches the original implementation across 5 test cases including special characters.\n   110→- Added 'status' to import-boundaries MODULE_NAMES to ensure boundary enforcement.\n   111→\n   112→### Debug Log\n   113→\n   114→No issues encountered during implementation.\n   115→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01VNjZAjpP2pH4BGjYH7gZ11","session_id":"a74f233b-d75f-4731-af98-d5f8de661326","uuid":"fe3a6178-3787-4046-a6b8-1a842d11fef4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:42:06.082Z"}
