{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VNjZAjpP2pH4BGjYH7gZ11","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Review complete.** Story 12-3 status updated to `verifying`.\n\n**Summary of actions:**\n- Reviewed all 7 files in the story's File List against git reality and acceptance criteria\n- Found and fixed 3 MEDIUM issues (unused imports, missing test mock)\n- All 3493 tests pass, 0 regressions\n- Coverage: 97.09% overall, all 150 files above 80% per-file floor\n- Command reduced from 745 to 56 lines (well under 100-line NFR5 target)\n- Both ACs verified: AC1 (command under 100 lines), AC2 (identical URL generation via comparison test)\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/status/formatters.ts` — removed unused imports\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/__tests__/status.test.ts` — added verify module mock\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/12-3-move-status-logic-to-module.md` — status to verifying, review notes, changelog\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- MEDIUM: Unused import `isSharedStackRunning` in `src/modules/status/formatters.ts` — dead code from extraction; would cause lint warnings and confusion about actual dependencies\n- MEDIUM: Unused type import `DockerHealthResult` in `src/modules/status/formatters.ts` — same dead code issue\n- MEDIUM: Missing mock for `modules/verify/index.js` in `src/commands/__tests__/status.test.ts` — `getValidationProgress` was being called without a mock; tests passed only because the function gracefully handles missing sprint-state.json in temp dirs. If that function's error handling changes, tests would break unexpectedly.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n- No dedicated unit tests for `formatters.ts` or `drill-down.ts` at the module level. The command-level integration tests in `status.test.ts` (80 tests) cover these thoroughly, but per the \"fat modules\" pattern, module-level tests would provide faster feedback and better isolation.\n- The `printSprintState()` and `handleFullStatusJson()` paths each independently call `generateReport()` / `getSprintReportData()` — while they're on separate code paths (human vs JSON), a shared data-fetching layer could reduce duplication if the status module grows further.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None below floor. All 150 files above 80%. Overall 97.09%.\n- `getValidationProgress` integration path is only implicitly tested (returns empty/zero data). No explicit test verifies the validation progress section renders correctly in status output. Covered indirectly by the mock returning `total: 0` which skips display.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. Cross-module imports correctly use public API (`index.js`). Import boundary enforcement is in place. Clean separation between command (arg parsing) and module (business logic).\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad88c6fe0ab5826d9 (use SendMessage with to: 'ad88c6fe0ab5826d9' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 75201\ntool_uses: 61\nduration_ms: 265417</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a74f233b-d75f-4731-af98-d5f8de661326","uuid":"f11031d6-93d3-420d-ad9a-4f96a73865ed","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:46:27.358Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/12-3-move-status-logic-to-module.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files below floor, untested edge cases, areas needing integration tests)\n- Architecture concerns (patterns that don't fit, coupling issues, missing abstractions)\n- Items sent back for re-development (what failed and why)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"ad88c6fe0ab5826d9","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Review complete.** Story 12-3 status updated to `verifying`.\n\n**Summary of actions:**\n- Reviewed all 7 files in the story's File List against git reality and acceptance criteria\n- Found and fixed 3 MEDIUM issues (unused imports, missing test mock)\n- All 3493 tests pass, 0 regressions\n- Coverage: 97.09% overall, all 150 files above 80% per-file floor\n- Command reduced from 745 to 56 lines (well under 100-line NFR5 target)\n- Both ACs verified: AC1 (command under 100 lines), AC2 (identical URL generation via comparison test)\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/status/formatters.ts` — removed unused imports\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/__tests__/status.test.ts` — added verify module mock\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/12-3-move-status-logic-to-module.md` — status to verifying, review notes, changelog\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- MEDIUM: Unused import `isSharedStackRunning` in `src/modules/status/formatters.ts` — dead code from extraction; would cause lint warnings and confusion about actual dependencies\n- MEDIUM: Unused type import `DockerHealthResult` in `src/modules/status/formatters.ts` — same dead code issue\n- MEDIUM: Missing mock for `modules/verify/index.js` in `src/commands/__tests__/status.test.ts` — `getValidationProgress` was being called without a mock; tests passed only because the function gracefully handles missing sprint-state.json in temp dirs. If that function's error handling changes, tests would break unexpectedly.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n- No dedicated unit tests for `formatters.ts` or `drill-down.ts` at the module level. The command-level integration tests in `status.test.ts` (80 tests) cover these thoroughly, but per the \"fat modules\" pattern, module-level tests would provide faster feedback and better isolation.\n- The `printSprintState()` and `handleFullStatusJson()` paths each independently call `generateReport()` / `getSprintReportData()` — while they're on separate code paths (human vs JSON), a shared data-fetching layer could reduce duplication if the status module grows further.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None below floor. All 150 files above 80%. Overall 97.09%.\n- `getValidationProgress` integration path is only implicitly tested (returns empty/zero data). No explicit test verifies the validation progress section renders correctly in status output. Covered indirectly by the mock returning `total: 0` which skips display.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. Cross-module imports correctly use public API (`index.js`). Import boundary enforcement is in place. Clean separation between command (arg parsing) and module (business logic).\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None."}],"totalDurationMs":265417,"totalTokens":75201,"totalToolUseCount":61,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":442,"cache_read_input_tokens":74005,"output_tokens":753,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":442},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
