{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019zXtR2BT5VE2UBk2JHNVKE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# src/lib/stacks — Stack Provider System\n     2→\n     3→Encapsulates per-language logic behind the `StackProvider` interface. Each provider implements detection, coverage, OTLP instrumentation, Dockerfile generation, and test parsing for one technology stack.\n     4→\n     5→## Files\n     6→\n     7→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n     8→|------|---------|-------------|\n     9→| types.ts | Canonical type definitions — `StackProvider` interface, `StackName`, `AppType`, coverage/OTLP/test types | `StackProvider`, `StackName`, `AppType`, `CoverageToolName`, `CoverageToolInfo`, `OtlpResult`, `TestCounts` |\n    10→| registry.ts | Provider registry — registration, lookup, marker-based stack detection | `registerProvider`, `getStackProvider`, `detectStacks`, `detectStack`, `StackDetection`, `_resetRegistry` |\n    11→| nodejs.ts | Node.js provider — app type detection, coverage (c8/vitest/jest), OTLP packages, Dockerfile (node:22-slim), test output parsing | `NodejsProvider` |\n    12→| python.ts | Python provider — app type detection, coverage (pytest-cov), OTLP packages, Dockerfile, test output parsing | `PythonProvider` |\n    13→| rust.ts | Rust provider — Cargo.toml parsing, coverage (tarpaulin), OTLP packages, multi-stage Dockerfile (rust:1.82-slim), workspace test aggregation | `RustProvider` |\n    14→| utils.ts | Shared helpers for providers — safe JSON/text reading, Node.js/Python/Cargo dependency extraction | `readJsonSafe`, `readTextSafe`, `getNodeDeps`, `getPythonDepsContent`, `hasPythonDep`, `getCargoDepsSection`, `hasCargoDep` |\n    15→| index.ts | Barrel re-exports + auto-registers NodejsProvider, PythonProvider, RustProvider on import | all public API from types.ts and registry.ts |\n    16→\n    17→## Architecture\n    18→\n    19→- `StackProvider` interface in `types.ts` defines the contract (15 methods, 1 optional)\n    20→- Each stack gets its own file (`nodejs.ts`, `python.ts`, `rust.ts`)\n    21→- `registry.ts` stores providers in a module-level `Map<StackName, StackProvider>`\n    22→- `index.ts` triggers auto-registration on import\n    23→- `utils.ts` provides shared filesystem helpers used across providers\n    24→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01LpBFDE1KxDokaruyokqTrj","session_id":"a74f233b-d75f-4731-af98-d5f8de661326","uuid":"1c69ad41-76d7-4c7c-824d-235298b41edd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:48:55.017Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q4CPagAhb1svoB6QPEgtgf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# src/lib — Shared Libraries\n     2→\n     3→Pure library modules consumed by CLI commands (`src/commands/`) and by each other. No CLI entry points, no side effects on import.\n     4→\n     5→## State & Output\n     6→\n     7→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n     8→|------|---------|-------------|\n     9→| state.ts | YAML front-matter state persistence in `.claude/codeharness.local.md` | `readState`, `writeState`, `readStateWithBody`, `getStatePath`, `HarnessState` |\n    10→| output.ts | Structured `[OK]/[FAIL]/[WARN]/[INFO]` CLI output with JSON mode | `ok`, `fail`, `warn`, `info`, `jsonOutput` |\n    11→\n    12→## Stack Provider System\n    13→\n    14→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n    15→|------|---------|-------------|\n    16→| stacks/types.ts | Canonical stack type definitions and `StackProvider` interface | `StackProvider`, `StackName`, `AppType`, `CoverageToolName`, `CoverageToolInfo`, `OtlpResult`, `TestCounts` |\n    17→| stacks/registry.ts | Provider registry with marker-based stack detection | `registerProvider`, `getStackProvider`, `detectStacks`, `detectStack`, `StackDetection`, `_resetRegistry` |\n    18→| stacks/nodejs.ts | Full NodejsProvider — all Node.js-specific logic extracted from consumer files | `NodejsProvider` |\n    19→| stacks/python.ts | Full PythonProvider — all Python-specific logic (app type detection, coverage, OTLP, Dockerfile, pytest parsing) | `PythonProvider` |\n    20→| stacks/rust.ts | Full RustProvider — Cargo.toml parsing, tarpaulin coverage, OTLP packages, multi-stage Dockerfile, workspace test aggregation | `RustProvider` |\n    21→| stacks/utils.ts | Shared helpers for stack providers — JSON/text file reading, Node.js/Python/Cargo dependency extraction | `readJsonSafe`, `readTextSafe`, `getNodeDeps`, `getPythonDepsContent`, `hasPythonDep`, `getCargoDepsSection`, `hasCargoDep` 